d was unavoidable better follow up was an absolute necessity not fulfilled resulting in a situation in which the people of libya are arguably worse off now than they were under the deeply flawed leadership of muammar gaddafi these seemingly incongruous positions he argues demonstrate that consistency when it comes to foreign relations is a bad idea and that each situation requires a customfit approach maintaining a consistent interventionist or conversely noninterventionist foreign policy for example would be a mistake bibliographyedit beyond the inf treaty  isbn  the power to persuade how to be effective in any unruly organization  isbn  updated in  as the bureaucratic entrepreneur how to be effective in any unruly organization  isbn  economic sanctions and american diplomacy  isbn  the reluctant sheriff the united states after the cold war  isbn  after the tests us policy toward india and pakistan  isbn  transatlantic tensions the united states europe and problem countries editor  isbn  intervention the use of american military force in the postcold war world  isbn x “imperial america”  honey and vinegar incentives sanctions and foreign policy  isbn  the opportunity americas moment to alter historys course  isbn  war of necessity war of choice  isbn  foreign policy begins at home the case for putting americas house in order  isbn  a world in disarray american foreign policy and the crisis of the old order  isbn  referencesedit  httpwwwnndbcompeople  drezner daniel w december   a politically incorrect take on the gop foreign policy debate the washington post retrieved july     a b haass talks bbc news january   retrieved january     the reluctant sheriff the united states after the cold war  richard haass  google books booksgoogleca  isbn  retrieved    published november    paid notice deaths haass irving b  new york times nytimescom retrieved    richard n haass biography council on foreign relationsorg retrieved january     richard n haass  council on foreign rela