 the planet there was no world order for the us to lead until soviet evisceration effected via clandestine sinous strategic collaboration in central america southern africa and the horn south asia indochina and most spectacularly afghanistan supplanted bipolarity at the systemic core with unipolarity although large swathes of the worlds surface remained beyond its ken this postsoviet era could accurately be generalised as the usled liberal world order but such orders last only as long as major players acquiesce in it and accept their own subordination to the primate in late  when the cpccc and the cmc jointly identified the usa japan and the rok as the source of the most acute threats to chinese security and began preparing to deter intervention that voluntary subordination ended in  the dodona summer study similarly identified china as a constant competitor and later viewing it as a nearpeer rival america prepared to neutralise chinese challenges to us primacy by definition the system was no longer unipolar in a nonunipolar system again by definition there simply could not be a global order this is why it would be logical to state that the usdesignedandled order acquired and retained its virtually global character between the end of  when the ussr collapsed and the summer of  when beijing began girding itself against the systemic primate and certainly by the end of  when the executive and legislative branches in washington took policymeasures against chinas challenges to american primacy the globality of the usled order endedso when eminent analysts premise their analyses on assertions of a very shortlived usled order as the global norm then all inferences flowing from such analyses must logically be much more imperfect than the simple frailties of human cognition would warrant this would be a difficult methodology for delivering practical policy options read more reply comment commented steve hurst jun   a somewhat uscentric and egotistical point of view with no great review of some of the problems the us has caused as  million americans are on food stamps perhaps global domination is not top of their agendathe idea macron can save france by saving the eu is somewhat detached from reality it would be simple enough to save france by quitting the euro but that will not happen with macronbtw us fertility rates are a problem and on a downward drift and standing at  per woman  being needed for a stable population but hey dont let facts get in the way of a good story read more reply comment commented jagjeet sinha jun   take your pickthere have been several empires alexander the greatashoka the greatthe great khan genghisthe roman empirethe moghul empirethe british empireempires of religion will leave bloodshed all overempires of race  caste will create inequalities unlimitedempires of regions will mean permanent disequilibriumtake your pick  for the most inclusivemy vote the cityonthehill shall remain in the anglosphere read more reply comment commented stephan edwards jun   the people of the us got tired mr haass they got tired of the leaders sacrificing their interests for others because it was necessary for our allies they got tired because they looked around realized since they didnt have to shoulder the burdens or sacrifices of guns or butter we paid for the guns they got the butter secondly and i am sure it is coincidental the well connected and powerful got very very rich by sacrificing the interests of the commoners they did a wonderful thing by letting china into the wto for china and the rich but not for people who watched their jobs shipped off to china because leadership means sacrifices must be made bluntly the withdrawal is because the commoners are so very tired of sacrifices i would suggest mr haass that if the sacrifices had been shared instead of strictly from those who had no voice in matters there might be some support for playing a leadership role but there was not and if frankly let others pay the price for 